1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,340
A smart contract is completely isolated from the outside world. It

2
00:00:05,440 --> 00:00:10,451
can't see what ETH costs on Coinbase. It can't access interest

3
00:00:10,551 --> 00:00:16,881
rates, stock prices, or weather data. Without external data, lending protocols

4
00:00:16,981 --> 00:00:24,383
can't calculate collateral values, options protocols can't settle, prediction markets can't

5
00:00:24,483 --> 00:00:30,813
resolve. The oracle problem is DeFi's most critical infrastructure challenge —

6
00:00:30,913 --> 00:00:34,028
and Chainlink is the dominant solution.

7
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:40,863
Welcome to QuantiFire. Chainlink is a decentralized oracle network that aggregates

8
00:00:40,963 --> 00:00:47,444
data from multiple sources and delivers it on-chain with cryptographic security

9
00:00:47,544 --> 00:00:52,942
guarantees. It powers over $75 billion in DeFi TVL across hundreds

10
00:00:53,042 --> 00:00:57,856
of protocols. Understanding how it works — and where it can

11
00:00:57,956 --> 00:01:02,521
fail — is essential for any DeFi participant or builder.

12
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:13,208
Chainlink's architecture: multiple off-chain premium data providers each provide

13
00:01:13,308 --> 00:01:18,658
price data independently. A network of independent node operators

14
00:01:18,758 --> 00:01:21,593
— typically 7 to 31 per feed — each

15
00:01:21,693 --> 00:01:26,792
independently query the data sources, aggregate them, and sign

16
00:01:26,892 --> 00:01:31,990
the result. An on-chain aggregator collects responses from all

17
00:01:32,090 --> 00:01:37,021
nodes, removes outliers, and reports the median on-chain. To

18
00:01:37,121 --> 00:01:41,382
corrupt a Chainlink feed, an attacker must corrupt a

19
00:01:41,482 --> 00:01:47,084
majority of node operators simultaneously — prohibitively expensive.

20
00:01:48,933 --> 00:01:54,374
The price is updated on-chain when price moves more than 0.5% from

21
00:01:54,474 --> 00:01:59,327
the last on-chain value — the deviation trigger — or when a

22
00:01:59,427 --> 00:02:05,792
heartbeat interval of typically 1 hour has passed. Current best practice: use

23
00:02:05,892 --> 00:02:10,997
Chainlink as the primary feed with a Uniswap TWAP as a circuit

24
00:02:11,097 --> 00:02:16,538
breaker. If Chainlink deviates from TWAP by more than 5%, halt the

25
00:02:16,638 --> 00:02:23,842
protocol and require manual intervention. Every DeFi protocol you interact with depends

26
00:02:23,942 --> 00:02:29,886
on oracle accuracy. Before using any protocol, check what oracle it uses

27
00:02:29,986 --> 00:02:32,657
and how many nodes back the feed.

28
